args:
Alex and Mym meet with the abyssians,
denizens of the deep sea, in Aquaphos. As the
abyssinian civilization lies on the precipice of
collapse, their priestess Tiana, together with
Alex and Mym, creates the Abyssal Bell and
seeks succor from the god of the sea, Leviathan.
Long, long ago, Aquaphos was a great isle\nthat floated atop the brilliant blue sea.

During the First War of Binding a thousand
years past, the seas raged and roiled in the
aftermath of the battle between the Holywyrm
and the Other.
The islanders sought aid from mainlanders,\nbut their pleas went unheard.
Thus, the islanders made a decision: they\nwould cast away their secluded lives above\nthe sea and start anew deep below its surface.

The people prayed to Leviathan, great god of
the ocean. In answer, Leviathan calmed the
stormy seas and guided their island deep
'neath its dark waters.
Worshipping the wyrm as their divine, they\nbuilt a city at the bottom of the sea, with its\nown unique culture and technology.
This was the origin of what became Aquaphos,\nKingdom of the Deep, as well as its people,\nthe abyssians.
...And that's the story passed down\nabout our city and our people's origins.
You're a curious people, being able to\nbreathe underwater and speak with fish.

Hee hee. You make it sound so special.
Now I'm blushing. See, we underwent a
distinctive evolution as we lived our lives
down here.

But though we were once at the height
of prosperity, my people have grown
increasingly troubled by a shortage
of resources and food.
If it's been gradually happening over the\ncourse of a millennium, surely there had\nalready been concern about it in the past?
Well, yes, there's signs people had been\nworried about it before. But we abyssians\nare short-lived compared to humans, so...
It kept getting pushed off to the next\ngeneration. And now the abyssians are\npaying for their short-sightedness.
If I recall correctly, the war broke out a\nthousand years ago because humans\nheedlessly ravaged nature.
The same kinds of things can happen on\nthe surface. It's not a problem with race;\nit's a problem with mindset.
I hate to say this, but in the end, I think\nit's a case of people ignoring problems\nif they don't affect them personally.
Now your people face their end. And their\nbest idea is to conquer the surface world\nto steal its resources for their own.
Yes. Time is ticking away until the plan is\nput into motion. We can't let that happen!
Princess Tiana, may I bend your ear for\na moment? I'd like to discuss matters to\ncome.
Very well. I'll be there presently.
She is the princess of our kingdom,\nand the priestess of the abyss.
She protects the god of the sea, offers\nprayers to him, and receives of his\nblessings. It is a vital role.
If she's such a big deal around here, why\ndoes she live in a private home like this?
Princess Tiana was banished from the\npalace for heresies in her capacity as\nthe priestess.
She stubbornly raised her objections to the\nsurface invasion.
She proposed a third option—neither\ninvasion nor our destruction, but to\nawaken the god of the sea.
That sounds like a good thing to me.\nWhat was their problem?
Leviathan's sleeping breath brings about\nnew life in new seas. Thus, he must never\nbe awakened.
This is part of the code in Aquaphos. And\nfor the priestess of the abyss to lead the\nway in suggesting that code be flouted...
She was banished. Tiana must've been\nconsidered an impediment to the pro-\ninvasion faction, too.
Yes. It is in fact Princess Tiana's mother,\nHer Majesty the Queen, who spearheads\nthe plan to breach the surface.
Wait, so Tiana was banished by her\nactual MOTHER for opposing her?!
She was. However, the princess acts most\ncourageously, guiding us all in order to\nprotect our people and kingdom both.
A ＂traitorous＂ young royal who brings\npeople together, huh? Sounds like\nsomeone else we know.
Ugh, thanks for reminding me!\nNow I miss him all over again.
Let's wake this Leviathan up from his nap\nand get ourselves to dry land already.
So this is the Abyssal Bell.
How beautiful. It is as the sea itself.
So we whack the thing and make it ring?\nIt won't break?
We need only offer mana unto it.\nWhat will ring is the sea.
The sea will respond to our prayers and\ncause a seaquake, which will resound like\na bell.
In any case, you'll understand when\nwe do it. Let us be off to see Leviathan.
Great Leviathan, we abyssians sit upon\nthe brink of ruin!
I beseech you deliver us from our peril!
Deliver you? I am but an instrument of\ndestruction.
But you are the god we revere!\nYour power is—
My power is that of the raging sea itself.\nIt swallows all and rips it asunder.\nMy very existence is a sin!
That cannot be. You were the one who\nsaved my people a thousand years ago!
I struck wave against wave to turn them to\nmere ripples. That is all.
The danger I am remains unchanged.\nThe only action I can be permitted is\nnever-ending sleep.
But the code... You do not foster new\nlife as you sleep, but rather remain in\nrepose to seal away your power?
Begone from here. Should you remain\nany longer, I cannot guarantee your\nsafety!
I'm about at my limit here, Tiana!
We have to flee. Better to live and\nfight another day.
